15,01        Romance under a yard sale sign

15,01My love how my heart longs to hear,
15,01Those sweet words from your lips.
15,01Which gives life to my soul,
15,01And strength to my body.

15,01Your lips of sweet caresses,
15,01Are only felt in my dreams.
15,01When will my arms be filled with you,
15,01And when will my eyes drink of your beauty.

15,01I live only for you,
15,01For one look at you,
15,01And everything I ever believeed in
15,01Fades to nothing

15,01How will you know of my heart's longing,
15,01Or the love waiting for your embrace.
15,01How will I profess my love,
15,01Under the swaying yard sale sign.

